    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.7.0-dev+1277-g9e66d27d3\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch LInux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.10.1,  kitty 0.24.4 (less observable)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal packer_exists = pcall(vim.cmd, [[packadd packer.nvim]])\r\nlocal packer = require(\"packer\")\r\nlocal load_plugin = function()\r\n  return packer.startup({\r\n    function(use)\r\n      use({ \"wbthomason/packer.nvim\" })\r\n      use({\r\n        \"rcarriga/nvim-notify\",\r\n        config = function()\r\n          vim.notify = require(\"notify\")\r\n          require(\"notify\").setup({\r\n            background_colour = \"#000000\",\r\n            render = \"minimal\",\r\n            stages = \"fade\",\r\n          })\r\n        end,\r\n      })\r\n    end,\r\n  })\r\nend\r\nvim.opt.lazyredraw = true\r\nvim.opt.laststatus = 3\r\nvim.opt.termguicolors = true\r\nload_plugin()\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. nvim\r\n2. Split vertical\r\n3. Move to new split\r\n4. Split horizontal\r\n5. Move to new horizontal split\r\n6. `:lua vim.notify(\"Hello\")`\r\n7. Cursor blinking in the intersection\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCursor stays on the buffer\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5826834/159028983-9b55be45-e9e2-4e71-b3ce-2455cec4596e.mp4\r\n\r\nI've found out that it's `lazyredraw` that trigger this. Sorry cannot create a more minimal repro\r\n\r\nEDIT: Apparently, i can reproduce it to albeit in an extremely rare case (i don't even know what i pressed, just quickly editing some text, and it suddenly blinking and moving for a sec) when `lazyredraw` is disabled.\r\n\r\n",
