            "body": "hmmm can still reproduce it, it's strange. I came up with a bit simpler config and even resetting my terminal config too. I started to think this is nvim-notify bug but sadly i cannot recreate the transition animation on my own to test this\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n-- file.lua\r\n-- Clone nvim-notify somewhere, add to rtp\r\nvim.cmd(\"set runtimepath+=~/nvim_debug/plugins/nvim-notify\")\r\nvim.cmd(\"hi WinSeparator guibg=NONE\")\r\nvim.opt.lazyredraw = true\r\nvim.opt.laststatus = 3\r\nvim.opt.termguicolors = true\r\nvim.notify = require(\"notify\")\r\nrequire(\"notify\").setup({\r\n  background_colour = \"#000000\",\r\n  stages = \"fade\",\r\n})\r\n\r\n-- nvim --clean file.lua\r\n-- source %\r\n-- :lua vim.notify(\"Hello\")\r\n-- Flickers\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5826834/159581278-4dbfb489-73a6-46cf-be82-63b956e003eb.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
