            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'm seeing this too. It happens continuously when my statusline (feline) refreshes. I don't have time right now to whittle down my config to a minimal repro, but my config is [here](https://github.com/b0o/nvim-conf) for reference.\r\n\r\nCan confirm that it only happens in particular layouts. It seems to happen when window corners don't meet in perfect `┼`. If they form a `├` or `┬`, the issue arises. Interestingly, it doesn't seem to happen with `┴` or `┤`.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21299126/164556752-785f1422-fe77-48ee-bc94-8392bab41f75.mp4\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>More screencasts</summary>\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21299126/164555818-d2052657-6cef-449c-b203-e992246e778e.mp4\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21299126/164554696-205161d6-6f14-48e2-a628-b61a5fc7017f.mp4\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
